      "name": "Ali Ramadhan"
    },
    "body": "This PR finally upgrades the checkpointer so it can restore large models that take up more than 50% of system memory. It used to create a model then restore the fields which allocates twice as much memory as needed. Now the data needed to restore the fields is passed to the model constructor so no double allocation. Some refactoring had to happen to make this possible.\r\n\r\nThis PR is also part 2/3 of making boundary conditions a field property.\r\n\r\nShould help a lot with #602 and #603.\r\n\r\nResolves #416\r\nResolves #417\r\n\r\nNote: This PR branches off #627.",
